<a href="/questions/508385-i-ve-just-read-it-but-i-don-t-understand">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/11474112-sheena"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1582198917i/11474112._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/11474112-sheena">Sheena</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">A cup of tea is known as &apos;the cup that cheers&apos;. Mma Ramotswe and Mma Makutsi are always drinking together bush tea and ordinary tea in their office. T<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">A cup of tea is known as 'the cup that cheers'. Mma Ramotswe and Mma Makutsi are always drinking together bush tea and ordinary tea in their office. They discuss their cases and make observations in general over tea. Mma Makutsi brews tea for everyone in the office. To the two Mmas, add Mma Sylvia Potokwani of the Orphan Farm who always welcomes and cheers visitors with tea and fruit cake. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
