<div id="review_34559458" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/34559458" />
    <a title="Will Byrnes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1526851-will-byrnes"><img alt="Will Byrnes" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1291462190p2/1526851.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/34559458?book_show_action=true">Oct 05, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Will Byrnes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Will Byrnes" href="/user/show/1526851-will-byrnes">Will Byrnes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer34559458" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9907184907831851725">This is #6 in The No. 1 Ladies Detective Agency series. Mma Rwatse lies on her bed and squeezes out a mysterious intruder who had hidden there. He flees sans pants that got caught on the bed. Is there any relationship between this stranger and the pumpkin that appears on her porch? Mma Makutsi is taking up dancing, hoping to meet a man. One of the apprentices at the car shop is dating a rich married woman and foolishly puts far too many eggs in that basket.<br/><br/>Smith continues along with his set of e</span>
  <span id="freeText9907184907831851725" style="display:none">This is #6 in The No. 1 Ladies Detective Agency series. Mma Rwatse lies on her bed and squeezes out a mysterious intruder who had hidden there. He flees sans pants that got caught on the bed. Is there any relationship between this stranger and the pumpkin that appears on her porch? Mma Makutsi is taking up dancing, hoping to meet a man. One of the apprentices at the car shop is dating a rich married woman and foolishly puts far too many eggs in that basket.<br /><br />Smith continues along with his set of endearing characters. While the book retains the charm of its predecessors, I felt that the series was running out of steam with number 5. It is still the case. He will need to offer something a bit more to make ensuing entries worth the time. <br /><br />If you are new to the series. I would stop, go back and read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/35744177" rel="nofollow noopener">The No. 1 Ladies' Detective Agency</a>. It makes a difference seeing the characters develop over the volumes.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9907184907831851725" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


